	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Fear Kite</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, May 6th 10:25 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I've had my SK for about 6 months now and am only level 42. I have tried alot of differetn places solo and with group, both have drawbacks. Groups you have to share the xp, but you get to kill more and get healed. Solo you get all the xp but have alot more downtime, but if you do it right downtime can be trimmed. I've read half of this page without seeing the much loved and much used tech. of Fear Kite. As soon as you get Fear and a darkness those should be selected as spells to use. ALWAYS pull with darkness as it is a snare. Then cast fear, it runs away SLOWLY as you walk behind it beatin on it without getting hit back. recast as needed and you'll see that it is a very usefull tactic and very profitable.<br><br>Sannayen Dreamslayeer<br>42nd DE SK<br>Tarew Marr</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
